<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="196" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,288,1287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,541,567]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 14.8–16.8; head length: 1.5–1.9; head width: 3.0–3.3; pronotal length: 2.6–3.3; pronotal width: 9.2–10.2; scutellum length: 7.2–8.0; scutellum width: 5.1–5.8; abdominal width: 8.2–9.4; length of antennal segments. I: 1.0–1.1; II: 1.2–2.1; III: 1.1–1.5; IV: 3.1–4.8; V: 6.3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="196" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,288,1287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,648,674]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all of its extension. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with brown to concolorous punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[159,253,720,747]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 18I</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin greenish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[823,916,720,747]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 18I</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with dark brown stripes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 18J</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[395,523,756,783]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim shallowly excavated, slightly convex in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[159,251,792,819]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup laminar, oblique, short, tapering to the base, and adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[419,547,828,855]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere golf club like, elongated, laterally bent; inner margin with carina ending close to the apex of the posterior lobe; posterior lobe somewhat developed and rounded distally; anterior lobe developed and rounded; outer margin black and thick (
<figureCitation box="[827,949,900,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with tufts of dense and long setae along lateral margins separated dorsally by narrow bridge; posterior face pentagonal, slightly swollen laterally (
<figureCitation box="[159,285,972,999]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5B–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim median excavation widely open with expansions acuminated, large, surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view; expansions with a tuft of setae; bottom of median excavation with a small central concavity (
<figureCitation box="[357,445,1044,1071]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[664,750,1044,1071]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 subrectangular, posterior margin almost straight; margins black; inner angles reaching basal third of valvifers 9; inner margins divergent from the middle of the plate. Valvulae 9 exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="196" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,288,1287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1152,1178]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Comments.</emphasis>
See comments of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[553,693,1152,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavatum">
<emphasis box="[553,693,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">H. clavatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, additionally 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[853,986,1153,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis box="[853,986,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">H. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the posterior lobe of the paramere rounded distally (
<figureCitation box="[348,434,1188,1215]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777070/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[496,634,1188,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavatum">
<emphasis box="[496,634,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">H. clavatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more acuminated (
<figureCitation box="[849,937,1188,1215]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1344,198,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys clavatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates. Abbteviations: lat 8—laterotergites 8; lat 9—laterotergites 9; vf 8—valvifers 8; vf 9—valvifers 9; x—tenth segment. (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777066/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1203,1224,1251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,288,1287]" box="[199,1203,1224,1251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1225,1251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the keel-like superior process of the genital cup (
<emphasis box="[1061,1125,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="196">crista</emphasis>
: crest)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
